Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    #!/bin/bash
    set -e

    ###########################################################################
    # Install runtime dependencies
    ###########################################################################
    apt-get update
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3-pip
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest
    apt-get clean
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    ###########################################################################
    # Prepare initial task data
    ###########################################################################
    # Create the directory hierarchy
    mkdir -p /home/user/profiles

    # Make the directory world-writable so that the non-root user who will
    # run inside the container can create additional files there.
    chmod 0777 /home/user/profiles

    # Populate the required call-stack dump with exactly 22 lines
    cat > /home/user/profiles/callstack.log << 'EOF'
malloc
free
malloc
memcpy
malloc
memcpy
free
read
write
read
malloc
free
memcpy
write
write
malloc
free
read
memset
memset
malloc
write
EOF

    # Make the input file read-only (not strictly required, but signals that it
    # must not be modified by the student).
    chmod 0444 /home/user/profiles/callstack.log

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author example@example.com
    Description "Container for profiling frequency task – provides initial data and pytest."

%help
    This Apptainer image contains the initial immutable state for the
    "function frequency" profiling task.  It provides:
      • /home/user/profiles/callstack.log  (22 lines of sample data)
      • pytest (pre-installed)

    Students are expected to create /home/user/profiles/function_frequency.log
    during their solve phase.